OCI Gains Most in Two Weeks After Mirae Asset ‘Buy’ Rating

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-07-20T00:31:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/oci-gains-most-in-two-weeks-after-mirae-asset-buy-rating.html
OCI Co. advanced the most in two
weeks in Seoul trading after Mirae Asset Securities Co. began
coverage with a “buy” rating, saying solar cell market in
 Germany  will recover. South Korea’s biggest maker of
polysilicon, used to make solar panels, rose 2.5 percent to
390,500 won as of 9:25 a.m. on the Korea Exchange. The benchmark
Kospi Index climbed 1.5 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
 sshin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net  